::Battera::

She walked back inside the ship and couldn't help but thinking about 
her situation.  She was a pred on a maximal ship.  ANd now tat she
had 
finished her part of the mission, she was stuck until she could take 
Iron Raptor to the embassy.  Until then, she would have to stay here 
and wait.  She felt down.  Yes she was happy about talking the leader 
into joining her for the peace talks, but she still felt so out of 
place here.  Most of the bots on the ship hardly noticed her.  And
the 
other ones didn't trust her. She sisn't know how to gain thier trust.
 
SHe only knew that she was not apart of thier group. But only a 
visitor.   She walked back towards her room and decided to go into 
hybernation again untill needed.  She walked down the hall and passed 
by the bridge.  She kept going and passed by the messhall.  She would 
reach her room shortly and hybernate.  She just wasn't wanted or 
needed around here.  She reached her room and sttod infront of the 
door.  She hung her head and knew that there just wasn't anything
else 
to do.  She opened the door and walked inside.  She went to the bed 
and layed down, folding her wings tightly against her slender body.  
She closed her eyes and went into hybernation mode.  She would awaken 
later on and see if she is needed.  She entered into teh deep sleep
of 
hybernation.  Nothing will wake her until her program wakes her up.
